-- Lexer error: `\v` is not a valid escape (#668). Inside a CHAR literal every
-- backslash-letter that is not a real escape used to be silently reduced to the
-- bare letter (`'\v'` -> `v`), never rejected — while the STRING lexer already
-- rejected the identical escape. The two paths now share one escape table, so a
-- char rejects `\v` with the same message a string does.
c : Char
c = '\v'
